        "body": "Not everything changes. Key continuities:\n\n- **Job cards**: Existing e-KYC verified MGNREGA job cards remain valid until new Gramin Rozgar Guarantee Cards are issued.\n- **Work within 15 days**: Employment must still be provided within 15 days of demand, failing which unemployment allowance is payable.\n- **5 km radius**: Work must be provided within 5 km of the applicant's village; beyond that, 10% transport allowance applies.\n- **Contractor ban**: No contractors or machinery may be used — employment must be manual.\n- **Gram Panchayat role**: At least 50% of works must be implemented by gram panchayats.\n- **Women's participation**: Minimum 33% of workers per worksite must be women (actual participation is now 58% nationally).\n- **DBT wages**: Wages continue through bank or post office accounts.\n- **Oral demand**: Workers may still demand employment orally, in writing (Form-6), or digitally.\n\n**Verified Fact.** Source: VB-G RAM G Act, 2025, transitional provisions; PIB, May 2026; Ministry of Rural Development FAQ. Confidence: 100."
