    "title": "India's Digital Regulation Offensive: DPDP Act Timeline Slashed, IT Rules Expanded, Crypto KYC Tightened",
    "summary": "India is advancing digital regulation on three fronts: DPDP Act compliance accelerated from 18 to 12 months, IT Rules amendments expand the Digital Media Ethics Code to individual news-sharing accounts, and the FIU is demanding OTC crypto records above $10,000 with mandatory live-selfie KYC. A single platform could simultaneously be a data fiduciary under DPDP, an intermediary under IT Rules, and a reporting entity under FIU guidelines.",
    "category": "Technology",
